jdc         2001/12/08 03:34:51 EST	(20011208_12)

  Modified files:
    src                  sprintf_irc.c 
  Log:
  - Change to ircsprintf().  Someone please look into this, as the change
  may affect daemon performance.  Here are the details:
  
  On RedHat Linux 7.1, gcc 2.96 seems to complain about trying to obtain
  the "address of a register" (in this case, args) in reference to the
  va_start() macro:
  
  "warning: address of register variable `args' requested"
  
  One can't get the _address_ of a CPU register, but I'm not sure if this
  is actually what's going on (due to va_start() being wacky as hell).
  
  This works on gcc 2.95.3 (FreeBSD 4.4-STABLE), though.  I have no idea if
  it's _ACTUALLY_ using a register or not.  Someone with gdb/gas knowledge
  should attempt to figure out what the heck is going on.
  
  Revision  Changes    Path
  1.10      +7 -2      ircd-hybrid-6/src/sprintf_irc.c



