  whitespace from end of lines, and minor definition changes.


*** 20010805_3 by leeh
- moved reason = parv[2]; up a step


*** 20010805_2 by jdc
- Removed unused variables in m_gline().
- Extra () to define truth in invalid_wildcard().
- Renamed 'local' to 'local_client' to avoid shadowing in invalid_gline().


*** 20010805_1 by leeh
- removed some #if 0'd code that doesnt need to be there


*** 20010804_2 by leeh
- changed some defaults


*** 20010804_1 by leeh
- we are now TS5
- added a doc describing the protocol changes
- TS5 will do the following:
  - TS rules are *always* obeyed, whether the channel is opless or not,
    whereas TS3 would allow ops from a channel merge on an opless channel,
    TS5 will NOT do this, the oldest channel will always win
  - this behaviour is NOT a define, we cant support backward compatibility
    now, so supporting it 6 months on doesnt make sense


*** 20010803_1 by leeh
- extended the check in get_client_name to cover handshaking/connecting
  servers


*** 20010731_1 by lusky
test commit to new repository


*** 20010729_1 by db
- removed prohibition on servers removing +o etc.



*** 20010727_4 by jdc
- Whoops, typo (chat != char ;-) ).


*** 20010727_3 by jdc
- src/s_serv.c: show_capabilities():
    Removed the trailing space during link-time or anything involving
    listing capabilities.  Also added error check for links without
    caps.


*** 20010726_2 by leeh
- added #define HIDE_ERROR_MESSAGES, as when we receive an error from a 
  server, theyll sometimes send their IP along with it..


*** 20010726_1 by leeh
